cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and learning phonetic structures from audio and text embeddings. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech data and cs.LG (Learning) as it involves machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves learning from a small amount of data, which is a common problem in social networks.
